{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "vPIM follows a virtio-based para-virtualization approach to facilitate its quick adoption by cloud users and providers.",
    "vPIM includes a set of optimizations to minimize virtualization overhead.",
    "We evaluated vPIM using unmodified applications provided by PrIM [31] and UPMEM.",
    "The results showed that some applications generate many guest-hypervisor-VMM transitions, drastically increasing virtualization overhead.",
    "For future work, we plan to investigate the vhost_vsock approach [8] to reduce the cost of performing guest-hypervisor-VMM transitions and enhance PIM device sharing across workloads."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
